</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="94.[124,654,193,1155]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
ETYMOLOGY: The trivial name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[573,653,1044,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calvus">
<emphasis box="[573,653,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">calvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(bald) is a Latin adjective used here to emphasize the lack of a setal tuft on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
